      "subtitles": [
        {
          "at": 1,
          "text": "We’ve already learned how to use “多少” to ask about quantity,"
        },
        {
          "at": 5,
          "text": "for example, “她有多少个学生？”."
        },
        {
          "at": 8,
          "text": "Now let’s look at “几”."
        },
        {
          "at": 12,
          "text": "We use “几” when the number is small, usually under 10."
        },
        {
          "at": 15,
          "text": "For example: “你有几个姐姐？” “你家有几口人？”."
        },
        {
          "at": 22,
          "text": "So here’s a simple rule. "
        },
        {
          "at": 24,
          "text": "If the number is large, use “多少”."
        },
        {
          "at": 28,
          "text": "If the number is small, under 10, use “几”. "
        },
        {
          "at": 32,
          "text": "Very clear, right?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "type": "content",
      "title": "第 2 页",
      "audio": "narration/2.mp3",
      "subtitles": [
        {
          "at": 1,
          "text": "There’s one more thing to remember. "
        },
        {
          "at": 3,
          "text": "When you use “多少”, the measure word can be used, or it can be left out."
        },
        {
          "at": 8,
          "text": " For example, you can say “你有多少个学生？”, or simply “你有多少学生？”."
        },
        {
          "at": 15,
          "text": "But when you use “几”, the measure word is required. "
        },
        {
          "at": 19,
          "text": "You must say “你有几个姐姐？”. You cannot say “你有几姐姐？”. Keep this in mind."
        }
      ],
